-- Gran Tierra Confirms Kidnapping of Colombian Contractors
-- B y   A n a t o l y   K u r m a n a e v
-- 2013-01-31T14:18:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-31/gran-tierra-confirms-kidnapping-of-colombian-contractors.html
Three contractors providing services
to  Gran Tierra Energy Inc. (GTE)  were “illegally detained” in the
Putumayo Basin in southern Colombia, the company said  today in
a statement on PR Newswire.  RCN Radio  cited a local government official who said the
three workers were kidnapped by guerrillas from the
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia, or FARC.  Gran Tierra is a Calgary-based oil producer, with
operations in Colombia and  Argentina . The company has early
stage exploration operations in Cauca, according to a
presentation on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anatoly Kurmanaev in Bogota at 
 akurmanaev1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Matthew Bristow at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net  